      "body" : "@Abdul: there is no “difference between just in space and speed”, as <code>int</code> in Java is a primitive type. The methods for using these primitive values as unsigned are located in the class <code>Integer</code>, but this doesn’t imply that you need <code>Integer</code> objects (these methods are <code>static</code>)."
