      "comment_id" : 131701286,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@MohammadKholghi casting an int to long will sign-extend (i.e., if the int would be negative, the long will be negative). in effect this means all upper bits of the long get set to 1. if you mask against 32 bits, you will get only those 32 bits, so it will always be positive.  the &quot;L&quot; at the end makes it a long literal rather than an int"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 133137,
      "reputation" : 13710,
      "user_id" : 334270,
